cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

The paper focuses on natural language processing and recommendation systems for scientific literature, which are topics that are commonly found in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). The use of a knowledge graph and graph inference also suggests a potential overlap with the sub-category of knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI).
